name: Himalayas - Breathable Nail Polish
description: Himalayas [him-uh-ley-uh-z] is inspired by the pink rock salt mined near the Himalayan mountains of Punjab, Pakistan. The Himalayan pink salt is found in the Khewra Salt Mine, one of the oldest and largest salt mines in the world and the salt itself is thought to have been created millions of years ago. This salt mine was discovered by Alexander the Great's troops in 320 BC, and the story is that the sick horses of his troops licked the stone and recovered, leading to the belief held today by many that the salt is loaded with minerals and provide health benefits.

name: Cusco - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
This deep mauve pink is inspired by the stunning rainbow mountain of Cusco, Peru. Known as Vinicunca, or the mountain of seven colors, the mountain is considered a holy site in Peru. Cusco is the former capital city of the Incas, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, and the oldest continuously inhabited city in the Americas.

Cusco is a deep mauve pink cream. Cusco is darker and cooler than Jaipur and less bright compared to Monduli.

name: Abu Dhabi - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
This creamy white is inspired by the stunning Grand Mosque of Abu Dhabi, U.A.E. The Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque is considered the largest example of marble mosaic in the world. One of the world’s largest mosques, its features 82 domes, 24 carat gold chandeliers, 1,000 columns, and the largest hand-knotted carpet.

Abu Dhabi [ah-boo dah-bee] is as a bold white, the creamy texture of the formula providing an opaque look.

name: Kashmir - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
Our best-selling color is inspired by Kashmir’s traditional tea, Kashmiri chai and the pink blossoms and tulips of the Mughal Gardens. A World Heritage Site, the terraced gardens are coated with flowers, have a mountain backdrop, and are filled with the rich history of the Mughal empire.

Kashmir [kazh-meer] is best described as an opaque dusk purple color - with a slightly pink tone.

name: Sakura - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
Sakura [saa-kur-uh] is inspired by the stunning pale pink cherry blossoms found in Sakura, Japan. In fact, the most common of all the cherry blossoms are called "Sakura" or Japanese Cherry. Located in Chiba prefecture, Sakura has been inhabited since prehistory and is home to the National Museum of Japanese History. Sakura blossoms are seen as a symbol of renewal, rebirth and new beginnings. Sakura blossoms only bloom for a brief time - best viewed during Spring time in Japan.

Sakura is best described as a muted pink nude, nearly opaque with two coats.

name: Beirut - Breathable Nail Polish
description: This warm nude pink color was inspired by the beautiful and fascinating Lebanese city of Beirut. One of the oldest cities in the world, Beirut is known for its rich history, its beautiful coast, and its vibrant culture - even being called the "Paris of the East." This amazing city is home to Byzantine Mosaics, extravagant mosques and cathedrals, roman baths, ancient streets, and ruins from the Canaanite and Ottoman eras. One of the famous landmarks off the coast of Beirut, Pigeon's Rock, is known to have been the site of some of the oldest evidence of human existence was found. It is also claimed to be the remains of the sea monster the green hero Perseus killed to save Andromeda, having used Medusa's head to turn the monster into stone.

It is also claimed to be the remains of the sea monster the green hero Perseus killed to save Andromeda, having used Medusa's head to turn the monster into stone.

name: Cappadocia - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
This gorgeous rose gold is inspired by the magical region of Cappadocia in Turkey. Cappadocia is famous for its unique rock formations, ancient history, and hot air balloons, making it one of Turkey's most popular natural wonders & tourist attractions. The landscape of the region is filled with soft volcanic rock that has turned into hundreds of strangely shaped pillars, cones, and "fairy chimneys", in various colors and with churches, chapels, and monasteries hollowed into the rocks.

Best described as a pearly and opaque rose gold finish.

name: Goychay - Breathable Nail Polish
description: Goychay [goe-shay] is inspired by the Azerbaijani city famous for its pomegranate growing industry and its pomegranate festival. This annual cultural festival features a parade with traditional Azerbaijani dances and music, a marketplace with craftsmen and artists displaying their work, and of course an exhibition of all the different pomegranate dishes and products.

name: Patagonia - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
This mint aquamarine is inspired by the Marble Caves of Patagonia, Chile. The Marble Caves, also called the Capillas de Mármol, formed over the last 6000+ years as water melted from nearby glaciers and washed up against solid rocks slowly carving out the caves. Over time, the minerals in the water caused the caves to have blue, green, aquamarine, yellow, and black hues.

Patagonia is a light, mint aquamarine halal nail polish. Patagonia is more green toned than Azores.

name: Provence - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
This stunning light purple is inspired by the beautiful city of Provence, France. Provence is known for its beautiful landscape, surrounded by the river valleys, gorges, coastlands, and mountains. Provence is best described as a cool toned light purple. Provence is lighter in color than Jakarta.

name: Tuscany - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
This lovely burnt sienna shade is inspired by the Italian region of Tuscany, the fifth largest region in Italy. The terracotta clay rooftops of Tuscan homes inspired this nail polish color name. Known for art, history, beautiful landscapes and home to the cities of Florence, Siena, and Pisa, Tuscany is regarded as the birthplace of the Italian Renaissance.

Tuscany is a burnt sienna halal nail polish color with red undertone.

name: Komodo - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
This pink is inspired by the Indonesian island, Puluo Komodo. Home to over 4,000 Komodo dragons, volcanic hills, savannahs, forests, and Pantai Merah-The Pink Beach. This beach gets its striking color from microscopic single-celled organisms called foraminifera, which produce a red pigment on the coral reefs. This mixed with the white sands give the waters a stunning pink color that the island is famous for.

Komodo is an elegant, light amaranth pink nail polish. Komodo is lighter and less bold than Nizwa.

name: Kabul - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
This light brown nude is inspired by Kabul, Afghanistan - a city that has existed for over 3,500 years. The city is situated in a valley between the Hindu Kush mountains and has a rich history, from being a part of the Achaemenid Empire to being a key location of the Silk Road to seeing both British and Soviet rule. The city continues to develop and is known for its beautiful gardens, palaces, and mosques.

Kabul [ke-bool] is a light brown nude color, perfect for everyday wear.

Nizwa is inspired by the beautifully fragrant rose gardens of Oman's Jebel Akhdar, or "green mountain" which is located in the city of Nizwa. name: Alexandria - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
This pink beige shade is inspired by the Egyptian city of Alexandria, also referred to as the “Pearl of the Mediterranean.” Founded by Alexander the Great in 331 BC, Alexandria is the largest city on the Mediterranean and known for its rich culture and ancient history. Alexandria is famous for the great lighthouse Pharos which is one of the Seven Wonders of the Ancient World, for its legendary great library, and for the Catacombs of Kom el Shoqafa, one of the Seven Wonders of the Middle Ages.

Alexandria is a delicate, light pink beige. This color is more pink than Dakar, but more nude than Komodo.

The Agra Fort comprises of beautiful architecture such as the Jahangir Palace, the Khas Mahal, Diwan-I-Khas, and two beautiful mosques.

Not only will you find the beautiful painted city rich in color, but it is also rich in history as it is home to ancient temple pyramids.

name: Monduli - Breathable Nail Polish
description: Monduli is inspired by Lake Natron which is located in the town of Monduli, Tanzania. This lake is rich in minerals, giving the water its stunning red, orange and pink hues. Despite the high alkaline content, Lake Natron is known for being a breeding ground for over 75% of the World's flamingo population. The town of Monduli is also known for its memorable Monduli Mountains and the famous volcano Ol Doinyo Lengai, which is Maasai for "Mountain of God".

name: Cordoba - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
This vibrant red hue is inspired by the famous Mezquita of Córdoba, Spain and the annual flower festival hosted there each year in the spring. The Mezquita-Cathedral has been a place of worship for ancient Romans, Muslims, and Catholics over the course of history and considered a wonder of Moorish architecture with its peppermint-striped voussoirs. The flower festival, Fiesta de los Patios, is where the residents open their private patios to the public, revealing fluorescent flowers and fragrant fruit trees, a tradition in place for over 100 years.

Cordoba [kor-duh-buh] is a bright warm coral halal nail polish. Cordoba is brighter and pinker than Marrakech and more vivid and warm than Jaipur- a perfect summer polish!

description:
This metallic silver is inspired by the fifth richest nation in the world, Brunei [broo-nei]. One of the traditional forms of art in this country is silverwork or silver crafting, an ancient practice that is now known to be a profitable industry for the cottages. This sultanate nation is also known as having incredible mosques, lush forests, and the famous village of Kampong Ayer that is entirely on stilts over water.

Brunei is best described as a vivid silver with a metallic foil finish.

name: Rotomahana - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
Rotomahana's iridescent light white-pink color is named after Lake Rotomahana in New Zealand, and inspired by the pink and white terraces, also known as Te Otukapuarangi - Maori for the fountain of the clouded sky. This natural wonder was once considered the largest silica sinter deposit in the world and was sometimes referred to as the 8th wonder of the world in the 1800s. In 1886, Mount Tarawera erupted and the terraces were thought to have been destroyed.

Rotomahana is an almost-iridescent light pink breathable nail polish.

This volcanic geological formation of sand dunes consists of sands in seven distinct colors - red, brown, violet, green, blue, purple, and yellow - creating beautiful patterns into the hillside. Chamarel is also known for its other scenic locations like the Chamarel Falls, Ebony Forest, and the Black River Gorges National Park.

name: Baghdad - Breathable Nail Polish
description: This nude color was inspired by the sandy capital of Iraq, Baghdad [buhg-dad]. Once known as the world’s “centre of learning” and the largest city of the Middle Ages, the city was significantly destroyed by the Mongols in the 13th century and then again by the 2003 Invasion of Iraq. Though many of the cultural and historical pieces of the city are gone, there are still some that stand today, like the Al-Khulafa Mosque. This 10th century mosque dates back to the abbasid era and its sand-toned architecture is the main inspiration for the color.

description: Jaipur [jahy-poor] is inspired by the “the pink city” of India, a color scheme that’s enforced by local law and seen on every building in the city. In the late 1870’s, In order to impress the royal English family, the Maharaja of Jaipur painted the entire city pink as it was a color that represents welcoming and hospitality. His wife loved the color and had him pass a law that made it illegal for the building to be painted any other color.

name: Uluru - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
This muted redwood colored nail polish is inspired by and named after the large sandstone rock formation found in Australia. Uluru, or Ayers Rock, is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and is sacred to the aboriginal people of the area. The monolith has rich indigenous history and myths and legends surrounding it that go back thousands of years. The area around the formation has ancient paintings, rock caves, springs and waterholes and is known to give off a reddish pink hue in the sunlight.

Uluru is a muted redwood nail polish with cool brown undertones. Uluru is more brown and less saturated than Cusco.

name: Bahrain - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
This lovely iridescent polish was inspired by the sovereign state of Bahrain. This now island kingdom, has been claimed by the British, the Portuguese, and was also sought after by Iran - but it was originally a mercantile civilization called Dilmun. Throughout history, Bahrain has been famous for its pearl trade and pearl diving, which inspired this pearly and iridescent color.

Bahrain is best described as an iridescent and pearly finish. This can be worn alone or over another color as a topcoat, adding a beautiful, cool color shift.

name: Ostuni - Breathable Nail Polish
description: This vivid cool-white is inspired by the Italian “white city,” Ostuni. The medieval walled city is made up of stark white washed buildings sitting atop a hill with views of a beautiful countryside. The history behind the white walls is actually attributed to a plague in the 17th century. Apparently homes that were painted white had less illness and the locals believed it to be a miracle.

It's also famous for its beautiful view of the Northern Lights in winter and the Midnight sun in summer.

name: Guanajuato - Breathable Nail Polish
description: This beautiful red shade was inspired by the Mexican city of Guanajuato, also called the land of legends, known for its rich history, fascinating legends, and colorful buildings. The most famous alley is the Callejón del Beso or Alley of the Kiss. Located on the slopes of a hill in a neighborhood that dates back to the 18th century, the legend says that couples who kiss on the third step (painted in red) are guaranteed seven years of happiness together.

name: Dhofar - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
This shimmering bold pink is inspired by the city Dhofar in Oman. Marco Polo once wrote of Dhofar in his book, calling it a great and noble city and highlighting its frankincense trade - something Dhofar has been famous for since ancient times. The "Land of Frankincense" is a UNESCO World Heritage Site in Dhofar consisting of frankincense trees and the remains of a caravan oasis and two ports, which were crucial to the medieval incense trade. Also in Dhofar is the fabled lost city of Ubar that was found deep in the sands. Known as the "Atlantis of the Sands" it was mentioned in "A Thousand and One Nights" as a vital frankincense trade hub. Along with its incense trade, Dhofar is also famous for its beautiful lagoons, lakes, and the beautiful coastal cliffs and sandy beaches and is a great place to spot dolphins, cranes, and the pink flamingos that inspired this color.

Dhofar is best described as a hot pink cream color, with a hint of shimmer. Dries semi-matte!
